Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated HbA1c, indicating suboptimal long-term glycemic control, and mildly increased total cholesterol and triglycerides, suggesting dyslipidemia. Renal function, electrolytes, and urine microalbumin/creatinine ratio are within normal limits. Continued monitoring and optimization of diabetes and lipid management are recommended to reduce cardiovascular risk.
